<%- model_class = Gallery -%>
<div class="page-header">
  <h1><%=t '.title', :default => model_class.model_name.human.pluralize %></h1>
</div>

<table class="table table-striped">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th><%= model_class.human_attribute_name(:name) %></th>
      <th><%= model_class.human_attribute_name(:photos) %></th>
      <th><%= model_class.human_attribute_name(:description) %></th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <% @galleries.each do |gallery| %>
      <tr>
        <td><%= link_to gallery.name, gallery_path(gallery) %></td>
        <td><%= gallery.photos.size %></td>
        <td><%= gallery.description %></td>
      </tr>
    <% end %>
  </tbody>
</table>
<% if user_signed_in? %>
  <%= link_to "New Gallery", new_gallery_path, :class => 'btn btn-primary' %>
<% end %>
<p>
<a href="https://github.com/tonydng/photo_gallery">This Photo Gallery</a> is a Rails project in version 3.2.13 with <a href="https://github.com/tonydng/photo_gallery/tree/master/spec/features">full integration test</a>. The main idea of this application is that it can let a user to sign up, login, create (read, update, delete) his/her own gallery, and upload photos to this gallery. Also it can let a user to make comments about other people's photos. Beside serving for PC, this website can be viewed from any mobile phones/ipads without spending time to resize the browser window because it is a responsive website.

Give it a try by using <b>newguest9@gmail.com</b> as a <b>login</b> and
<b>password</b> as a password to login the application.
</p>
<p><%= link_to "Try it for free!", new_user_registration_path, 
      class: 'btn btn-large btn-primary' %></p>